---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import BirdsOfPreyMap from '../components/BirdsOfPreyMap.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Birds of Prey — Andrew Cordivari" description="Birds of prey sightings near Boulder, Colorado from GBIF">
  <article class="page-content">
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1>Birds of Prey</h1>
      <p class="lead">Exploring raptor sightings in the Boulder, Colorado area using data from the Global Biodiversity Information Facility.</p>
    </div>

    <aside class="story-card">
      <p>Raptors fascinated me from an early age and I had the privilege of frequenting <a href="https://www.theraptortrust.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Raptor Trust</a> in Millington, New Jersey. Colorado is an incredible environment for these magnificent creatures and I've literally seen hundreds of bald eagles, golden eagles, kestrels, red-tailed hawks, and even a few species of owls while I've lived here.</p>
      <p>One of my favorite species is the Ferruginous Hawk. They don't live in the Northeast but are large enough that they share some similarities with golden eagles. I set up client-side requests that aggregate photos, descriptions, and location reports from multiple sources listed below. This was necessary to get the highest quality photos, descriptions, and genus classifications.</p>
    </aside>
  </article>

  <BirdsOfPreyMap />

  <section class="about-data">
    <h2>About This Data</h2>
    <p>
      This map displays recent bird of prey observations within 100 miles of Boulder, Colorado.
      The data comes from <a href="https://www.gbif.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GBIF</a>,
      an international network that aggregates biodiversity data from sources worldwide including
      eBird, iNaturalist, and museum collections.
    </p>
    <h3>Species Groups</h3>
    <ul class="species-list">
      <li><span class="dot red"></span> <strong>Accipitriformes</strong> — Hawks, eagles, kites, harriers, and Old World vultures</li>
      <li><span class="dot orange"></span> <strong>Falconiformes</strong> — Falcons and caracaras</li>
      <li><span class="dot blue"></span> <strong>Strigiformes</strong> — Owls</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-content {
    max-width: 720px;
    padding-top: 3.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);
    line-height: 1.0;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    max-width: 58ch;
  }

  .story-card {
    border-left: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 0 0 0 1.5rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .story-card p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .story-card p + p {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .story-card a {
    color: var(--color-text);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-border);
    transition: text-decoration-color 0.15s;
  }

  .story-card a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .about-data {
    margin-top: 3.5rem;
    padding-top: 2.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .about-data h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .about-data h3 {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .about-data p {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .about-data a {
    color: var(--color-text);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-border);
    transition: text-decoration-color 0.15s;
  }

  .about-data a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .species-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .species-list li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    padding: 0.625rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .species-list li:first-child {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .species-list strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .dot.red   { background: #ef4444; }
  .dot.orange { background: #f97316; }
  .dot.blue  { background: #3b82f6; }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .page-content {
      padding-top: 2.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
